<paragraph id="8BBC36A5FFCA350DFF79FF4027CEDFD5" blockId="12.[151,461,152,178]" box="[151,461,152,178]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">
<heading id="D0F481C9FFCA350DFF79FF4027CEDFD5" bold="true" box="[151,461,152,178]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" reason="1">
<taxonomicName id="4C034D26FFCA350DFF79FF4027CEDFD5" authority="Butler, 1870" authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1870" box="[151,461,152,178]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ceratrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B977EAB7FFCA350DFF79FF4027CEDFD5" bold="true" box="[151,461,152,178]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">
<emphasis id="B977EAB7FFCA350DFF79FF402721DFD5" bold="true" box="[151,290,152,178]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">Ceratrichia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B54FFCA350DFEC6FF4027CEDFD5" author="Butler" box="[296,461,152,178]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" refString="Butler, A. G. (1870 a) Catalogue of diurnal Lepidoptera described by Fabricius in the collection of the British Museum. London, Taylor and Francis, v + 303 pp., 3 pls. [&quot; 1869 &quot;]" type="book" year="1870" yearSuffix="a">
Butler, 
<number id="3DCB2482FFCA350DFE6AFF4027BCDFD5" box="[388,447,152,178]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" value="1870.0">1870</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBC36A5FFCA350DFF79FF0626EADD5C" blockId="12.[151,1436,222,751]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">
This is a relatively large genus of about 
<number id="3DCB2482FFCA350DFD8CFF07247DDF90" box="[610,638,223,247]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" value="20.0">20</number>
species, restricted to the Afrotropical region. Due to the variability of species and the marked sexual dimorphism in some species, there has been considerable confusion regarding this genus in the past (
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B54FFCA350DFE88FEFE27EADE58" author="Riley" box="[358,489,294,319]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" refString="Riley, N. D. (1925) Notes on the genus Ceratrichia (Lep., Hesperiidae). Annals and Magazine of Natural History, Series 9, 16, 405 - 416. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222932508633328" type="journal article" year="1925">
Riley 
<number id="3DCB2482FFCA350DFE43FEFE27EADE58" box="[429,489,294,319]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" value="1925.0">1925</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). The treatments by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B54FFCA350DFD3DFEFE2560DE58" author="Riley" box="[723,867,294,319]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" refString="Riley, N. D. (1925) Notes on the genus Ceratrichia (Lep., Hesperiidae). Annals and Magazine of Natural History, Series 9, 16, 405 - 416. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222932508633328" type="journal article" year="1925">
Riley (
<number id="3DCB2482FFCA350DFCCEFEFE2559DE58" box="[800,858,294,319]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" value="1925.0">1925</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B54FFCA350DFC72FEFF2235DE58" author="Evans" box="[924,1078,295,319]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" refString="Evans, W. H. (1937) A catalogue of the African Hesperiidae indicating the classification and nomenclature adopted in the British Museum. British Museum (Natural History), London, UK, 212 pp., 30 plates." type="book" year="1937">
Evans (
<number id="3DCB2482FFCA350DFC1FFEFF222EDE58" box="[1009,1069,295,319]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" value="1937.0">1937</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, however, have remained fairly stable for many years. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B54FFCA350DFE4DFE92248CDE04" box="[419,655,330,355]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" refString="Collins, S. C., Larsen, T. B. &amp; Warren-Gash, H. (2004) Notes on Afrotropical butterflies with the description of eleven new species and four new subspecies (Lepidoptera: Rhopalocera) - ABRI Research Paper No. 3. Metamorphosis, 14 (3), 63 - 110. [' 2003 ']" type="journal article">
Collins 
<emphasis id="B977EAB7FFCA350DFE10FE942430DE04" box="[510,563,330,355]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number id="3DCB2482FFCA350DFDA2FE932484DE04" box="[588,647,331,355]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" value="2004.0">2004</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
made some adjustments, and recently 
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B54FFCA350DFBBBFE9322F4DE04" author="Larsen" box="[1109,1271,331,355]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" refString="Larsen, T. B. (2013) Ceratricula and Flandria - two new genera of Afrotropical Hesperiidae (Hesperiinae (incertae sedis )) for species currently placed in the genus Ceratrichia Butler. Zootaxa, 3666 (4), 476 - 488. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3666.4.4" type="journal article" year="2013">
Larsen (
<number id="3DCB2482FFCA350DFB5AFE9322ECDE04" box="[1204,1263,331,355]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" value="2013.0">2013</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
removed four species to his new genera 
<emphasis id="B977EAB7FFCA350DFE55FEB6243DDEE0" box="[443,574,366,391]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">Ceratricula</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B977EAB7FFCA350DFD9BFEB624DADEE0" box="[629,729,366,391]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">Flandria</emphasis>
, for which there is no information on their early stages or food plants. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B54FFCA350DFF02FE4B278DDECC" author="Larsen" box="[236,398,403,427]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" refString="Larsen, T. B. (2013) Ceratricula and Flandria - two new genera of Afrotropical Hesperiidae (Hesperiinae (incertae sedis )) for species currently placed in the genus Ceratrichia Butler. Zootaxa, 3666 (4), 476 - 488. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3666.4.4" type="journal article" year="2013">
Larsen (
<number id="3DCB2482FFCA350DFEA5FE4B2785DECC" box="[331,390,403,427]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" value="2013.0">2013</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
recognised four principal colour patterns of 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D26FFCA350DFC71FE4A2221DECC" box="[927,1058,402,427]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ceratrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B977EAB7FFCA350DFC71FE4A2221DECC" box="[927,1058,402,427]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">Ceratrichia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. (
<taxonomicName id="4C034D26FFCA350DFB81FE4B22CFDECC" box="[1135,1228,402,427]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Justicia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="flava">
<emphasis id="B977EAB7FFCA350DFB81FE4B22CFDECC" box="[1135,1228,402,427]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">C. flava</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-, 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D26FFCA350DFB06FE4B2365DECC" box="[1256,1382,402,427]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ceratrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phocion">
<emphasis id="B977EAB7FFCA350DFB06FE4B2365DECC" box="[1256,1382,402,427]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">C. phocion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-, 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D26FFCA350DFA6CFE4B26E1DEA8" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ceratrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nothus">
<emphasis id="B977EAB7FFCA350DFA6CFE4B26E1DEA8" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">C. nothus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D26FFCA350DFEDFFE6F27DEDEA9" box="[305,477,439,462]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ceratrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argyrosticta">
<emphasis id="B977EAB7FFCA350DFEDFFE6F27DEDEA9" box="[305,477,439,462]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">C. argyrosticta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-groups), but found their genitalia very uniform. 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D26FFCA350DFBF1FE6E26D8DE95" authority="Joicey &amp; Talbot" authorityName="Joicey &amp; Talbot" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ceratrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="semlikensis">
<emphasis id="B977EAB7FFCA350DFBF1FE6E232EDEA8" box="[1055,1325,438,463]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">Ceratrichia semlikensis</emphasis>
Joicey &amp; Talbot
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C034D26FFCA350DFF00FE022725DE94" box="[238,294,474,499]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Justicia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="flava">
<emphasis id="B977EAB7FFCA350DFF00FE022725DE94" box="[238,294,474,499]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">flava</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group) is treated below (
<figureCitation id="13382A20FFCA350DFDA2FE0224B2DE94" box="[588,689,474,499]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1754,1776]" captionTargetBox="[150,1426,285,1719]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[141,1426,285,1720]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 9. Adults of Ceratrichia semlikensis, Kakamega Forest, Kenya. 1, at rest, 22 Sep 1991; 2, male sunbathing, 17 Jun 1991; 3, female sunbathing, 1 Jul 1990." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/251869/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">
Figure 
<number id="3DCB2482FFCA350DFD4FFE0324B2DE94" box="[673,689,475,499]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
), while living adult representatives of the three other groups are shown in 
<figureCitation id="13382A20FFCA350DFEEAFE262767DD70" box="[260,356,510,535]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1975,1997]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,966,1953]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,964,1953]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 8. Adult Ceratrichia spp. 1 – 2, C. phocion, Forêt de Yapo, Côte d’Ivoire, 4 Dec 1988; 3, C. brunnea, Kakamega Forest, Kenya, 19 Jul 1990; 4, C. mabirensis, Kakamega Forest, Kenya, 31 Aug 1995." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/251868/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">
Figure 
<number id="3DCB2482FFCA350DFEBDFE272767DD70" box="[339,356,511,535]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
: 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D26FFCA350DFE9EFE2727E8DD70" box="[368,491,510,535]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ceratrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phocion">
<emphasis id="B977EAB7FFCA350DFE9EFE2727E8DD70" box="[368,491,510,535]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">C. phocion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D26FFCA350DFE17FE272525DD70" authority="Bethune-Baker" authorityName="Bethune-Baker" box="[505,806,510,535]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ceratrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brunnea">
<emphasis id="B977EAB7FFCA350DFE17FE272475DD70" box="[505,630,510,535]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">C. brunnea</emphasis>
Bethune-Baker
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C034D26FFCA350DFCD9FE2725A1DD70" box="[823,930,510,535]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ceratrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nothus">
<emphasis id="B977EAB7FFCA350DFCD9FE2725A1DD70" box="[823,930,510,535]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">C. nothus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group), 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D26FFCA350DFBEAFE2722E0DD70" authority="Riley" authorityName="Riley" box="[1028,1251,510,535]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ceratrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mabirensis">
<emphasis id="B977EAB7FFCA350DFBEAFE27229DDD70" box="[1028,1182,510,535]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">C. mabirensis</emphasis>
Riley
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C034D26FFCA350DFB05FE272390DD71" box="[1259,1427,511,534]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ceratrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argyrosticta">
<emphasis id="B977EAB7FFCA350DFB05FE272390DD71" box="[1259,1427,511,534]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">C. argyrosticta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
- group).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBC36A5FFCA350DFF29FD9F26ECDD88" blockId="12.[151,1436,222,751]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">
No food plant records had been published, until 
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B54FFCA350DFD06FD9F2585DD38" author="Larsen" box="[744,902,582,607]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" refString="Larsen, T. B. (2005) Butterflies of West Africa. Vols. 1. &amp; 2. Apollo Books, Stenstrup, Denmark, 595 + 270 pp." type="book" year="2005">
Larsen (
<number id="3DCB2482FFCA350DFCADFD9E257DDD38" box="[835,894,582,607]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" value="2005.0">2005</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
reported MJWC’s observation that 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D26FFCA350DFAF7FD9E2714DDE4" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ceratrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="semlikensis">
<emphasis id="B977EAB7FFCA350DFAF7FD9E2714DDE4" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">Ceratrichia semlikensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
feeds on 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D26FFCA350DFE6BFDB22463DDE4" box="[389,608,618,643]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Isachne" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mauritiana">
<emphasis id="B977EAB7FFCA350DFE6BFDB22463DDE4" box="[389,608,618,643]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">Isachne mauritiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry id="F3147635FFCA350DFD69FDB324D7DDE4" box="[647,724,619,643]" name="Kenya" pageId="12" pageNumber="313">Kenya</collectingCountry>
. No information is yet available for other species of the genus, but given that they usually fly low down along the edges of paths and streams with low grass or along forest edges (T.B. Larsen pers. comm. 
<number id="3DCB2482FFCA350DFE26FD6B2400DDAC" box="[456,515,691,715]" pageId="12" pageNumber="313" value="2014.0">2014</number>
, authors’ observations), it seems likely that they will also be found to be grass feeders.
</paragraph>
